      • commentBlockRegexMatcher

        public static boolean commentBlockRegexMatcher​(java.lang.String str)
        Checks the method calling statement if it complies to Java conventions or not . Tries to match both javadoc style and C style comments (excluding // style).
        Parameters:
        str - The string that is going to be checked.
        Returns:
        true if the style of the statement complies to the Java conventions, false otherwise.
        API Note:
        Do not try to match the file line by line. Comments should be in a continuous state.
